<br>
First, I agree with the statement &quot;...certain things are morally wrong because of the effect they have upon each of us....&quot; I think I had stated as much early on.<br>
<br>
I believe that we disagree on what constitutes a &quot;moral&quot;. I think a &quot;moral&quot; is a principle relating to a set of principles, values, and virtues; a.k.a. a system of Ethics. I see our disagreement turning on a perception of what each other's system of ethics may look like. Here is an example:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;We are talking about two choices in how you live your life really. Do you have a moral standard and follow it, or do you allow popular trends to dictate right and wrong? I am not talking laws I am saying popular thought (you know like mini skirts - here today gone tomorrow).&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
